[{"client_msg_id":"ef134780-520a-4bc2-b94e-2af98372e47e","type":"message","text":"Is there a possible way to reset the camera to the instant when the figure is first displayed?","user":"UTX7DAUBE","ts":"1612886652.456800","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"adR","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Is there a possible way to reset the camera to the instant when the figure is first displayed?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1612886652.456800","reply_count":17,"reply_users_count":2,"latest_reply":"1612900383.470000","reply_users":["UQMHE3ER4","UTX7DAUBE"],"subscribed":false},{"client_msg_id":"6058914d-9f64-4e01-a527-5a6820621049","type":"message","text":"`autolimits(axis)` maybe?","user":"UQMHE3ER4","ts":"1612892006.458000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"jnZkB","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"autolimits(axis)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" maybe?"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1612886652.456800","parent_user_id":"UTX7DAUBE"},{"client_msg_id":"c59af047-a41e-4d9d-b504-1c72f6f79527","type":"message","text":"In a 2d plot, such as\n```fig, ax, plt = lines(rand(10))\nautolimits!(ax)```\n`autolimits!`  works","user":"UTX7DAUBE","ts":"1612898889.466100","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UTX7DAUBE","ts":"1612898948.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"q95f","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"In a 2d plot, such as\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"fig, ax, plt = lines(rand(10))\nautolimits!(ax)"}]},{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"autolimits!","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"  works"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1612886652.456800","parent_user_id":"UTX7DAUBE"},{"client_msg_id":"05516581-67f2-4448-b048-227ca3dc0408","type":"message","text":"But in a 3d plot, `autlimits!` throws  a method error  as it expects an `Axis` object as its only argument.  So, I got  `MethodError` for the following since `ax` is an `LScene`\n```xs = LinRange(0, 10, 100)\nys = LinRange(0, 15, 100)\nzs = [cos(x) * sin(y) for x in xs, y in ys]\nfig, ax, plt = surface(xs, ys, zs)\nautolimits!(ax)```","user":"UTX7DAUBE","ts":"1612899086.466500","team":"T68168MUP","edited":{"user":"UTX7DAUBE","ts":"1612899135.000000"},"blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"42QG","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"But in a 3d plot, "},{"type":"text","text":"autlimits!","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" throws  a method error  as it expects an "},{"type":"text","text":"Axis","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" object as its only argument.  So, I got  "},{"type":"text","text":"MethodError","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" for the following since "},{"type":"text","text":"ax","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" is an "},{"type":"text","text":"LScene","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":"\n"}]},{"type":"rich_text_preformatted","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"xs = LinRange(0, 10, 100)\nys = LinRange(0, 15, 100)\nzs = [cos(x) * sin(y) for x in xs, y in ys]\nfig, ax, plt = surface(xs, ys, zs)\nautolimits!(ax)"}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1612886652.456800","parent_user_id":"UTX7DAUBE"},{"client_msg_id":"8c93d81d-a776-4675-955d-c5016805256e","type":"message","text":"In a 3d plot it's `center!(scene)`. Here that would be `center!(fig.scene)`","user":"UQMHE3ER4","ts":"1612899168.467000","team":"T68168MUP","blocks":[{"type":"rich_text","block_id":"eTqs","elements":[{"type":"rich_text_section","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"In a 3d plot it's "},{"type":"text","text":"center!(scene)","style":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Here that would be "},{"type":"text","text":"center!(fig.scene)","style":{"code":true}}]}]}],"thread_ts":"1612886652.456800","parent_user_id":"UTX7DAUBE","reactions":[{"name":"+1","users":["UTX7DAUBE"],"count":1}]},{"clie